<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 RB005 Week 7 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Polish &amp; Store Page — Ready for Strangers · <strong>Course:</strong> Dream Game Studio · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week your game gets its <strong>store page</strong>: a title, a description, and an icon screenshot. The big question for everything: <strong>could a stranger play your game without your help?</strong></p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each store page. Before you imagine a real player seeing it, write what you think they will do.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Title:</strong> OBBY!!!! FREE ROBUX!!!!!
<strong>The game:</strong> a coin-collecting maze. There is no free Robux.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>A player joins because of this title. What do they expect? What do they do when they find a maze instead?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<blockquote>
<p><strong>Title:</strong> my game
<strong>Description:</strong> this is my game i made it in class</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>A stranger reads this page. Do they know what kind of game it is or what to do in it? Will they press Play? Why or why not?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<blockquote>
<p><strong>Title:</strong> Coin Castle: Escape the Tower!
<strong>Description:</strong> Collect 10 coins to unlock the castle door. Dodge the lava bridge and reach the roof to win!</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>A stranger reads this page. What do they know about the game before joining? What will they try to do first?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>This week the bugs are not in code — they are <strong>broken store pages</strong>. Read what each one is supposed to do, write your fixed version, then explain why the original was wrong and why your fix works.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — The title should be short, honest, and exciting. The game is a lava-jumping obby with a boss door at the end.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Broken title:</strong> 💯FREE PETS GIVING AWAY ROBUX SIMULATOR💯</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write a fixed title:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — The description should tell a stranger what the game is and what to do. The game is a maze where you collect 8 keys to open the exit.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Broken description:</strong> good game pls play</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write a fixed description (2–3 sentences):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — The icon should make the game look fun in one glance. This icon is a blurry screenshot of Roblox <strong>Studio</strong>, with the Explorer window, the toolbar, and a script editor all visible.</p>
<p><strong>Write what screenshot you would take instead (where in the game, what is in the shot, what is NOT in the shot):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now polish your own game's store page. Do these in order:</p>
<p><strong>Write 2 candidate titles for your game, then circle the one you choose:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Write your description (2–3 sentences — clear, honest, exciting):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Checklist hunt — test your game like a stranger and tick each one:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Spawn point is set — new players appear in the right place</li>
<li>[ ] The win works — you can actually finish the game</li>
<li>[ ] Every menu button does something</li>
<li>[ ] Instructions tell a stranger what to do</li>
<li>[ ] A stranger could play it without your help</li>
</ul>
<p>Send a photo or video of your icon screenshot and finished store page, then explain your choices. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I chose the title … because …</p>
<p>My description tells players …</p>
<p>For my icon, I took a screenshot of …</p>
<p>During the checklist hunt, I found …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) — but this week, make it a <strong>30-second trailer</strong>. Narrate your game like an advert that makes a stranger want to play. Try to use these words: <strong>title</strong>, <strong>description</strong>, <strong>icon</strong>, <strong>player</strong>, <strong>goal</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Say your game's title and what kind of game it is.</li>
<li>Show the coolest moment of your game while you talk.</li>
<li>Tell players the goal — what do they do to win?</li>
<li>End with one sentence that makes people want to press Play.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
